        }
      },
      {
        '@type': 'Question',
        name: 'How do I optimise for Google AI Overviews specifically?',
        acceptedAnswer: {
          '@type': 'Answer',
          text: 'Google AI Overviews draws primarily from pages that already rank well in Google\'s traditional organic index. Strong E-E-A-T signals, entity clarity through Organisation schema, and well-structured content that uses descriptive headings and declarative opening paragraphs are the primary optimisation levers. Unlike Perplexity, which uses live RAG, Google AI Overviews relies heavily on the existing organic ranking layer — meaning traditional SEO remains a prerequisite for AI Overview inclusion, with GEO-specific optimisations layered on top.'
