const tactics = [
  {
    step: '01',
    title: 'Establish entity clarity across the web',
    body: 'AI systems identify you by your entity — the machine-readable representation of your brand. Build and maintain consistent entity descriptions across your website schema, Wikidata, LinkedIn, Google Business Profile, and any industry directories relevant to your sector. Inconsistent entity descriptions across these sources cause AI retrieval systems to treat your brand as low-confidence and reduce citation frequency. The sameAs property in Organisation schema is the primary technical mechanism for linking your entity to authoritative third-party identifiers.'
  },
  {
    step: '02',
    title: 'Structure content for AI extraction',
    body: 'Generative search systems extract passages, not whole pages. Each section of your content should open with a 40–100 word declarative statement that directly answers a relevant question. Single-concept paragraphs, descriptive headings that match natural-language queries, and self-contained sections that read coherently without surrounding context are the structural characteristics that consistently improve citation rates across all major AI search surfaces.'
  },
  {
    step: '03',
    title: 'Deploy comprehensive schema markup',
    body: 'Structured data removes ambiguity for AI retrieval systems. Every content page should carry Article schema (with author and publisher referencing the Organisation entity by @id), FAQPage schema where FAQ sections exist, and BreadcrumbList schema to signal topical hierarchy. This schema layer tells citation selection systems that your content is attributed, dated, categorised, and linked to a verified entity — all factors that increase citation probability.'
  },
  {
    step: '04',
    title: 'Build topical authority through content clusters',
    body: 'No single page establishes topical authority for generative search. A cluster of pages — a pillar page addressing the topic comprehensively, supported by multiple detail pages exploring subtopics — signals to AI retrieval indexes that your domain owns the subject area. Cross-linking within the cluster reinforces the topical signal. A domain with shallow, isolated coverage of a subject is consistently outperformed in AI citation by a domain with deep, interconnected topical architecture.'
  },
  {
    step: '05',
    title: 'Optimise crawl access for AI user-agents',
    body: 'All the content quality in the world is irrelevant if AI crawlers cannot access your site. Review your robots.txt and explicitly allow the user-agents that matter: GPTBot, PerplexityBot, ClaudeBot, Anthropic-AI, Google-Extended, and Bingbot. Implement an llms.txt file that declares your domain\'s expertise and priority pages. These technical steps are the foundation on which all other generative search optimisation tactics depend.'
  },
  {
    step: '06',
    title: 'Monitor citations and iterate',
    body: 'Generative search visibility requires active measurement. Establish a monitoring programme that queries target AI platforms weekly with your priority search terms, records whether your brand is cited, and tracks citation accuracy and competitive share of voice. AI models update frequently — Perplexity\'s live RAG responds to content changes within weeks; Google AI Overviews within the typical crawl cycle. Regular monitoring reveals what is working, what competitors are doing better, and where new citation opportunities have emerged.'
