      <!-- Section 5: Relationship to GEO -->
      <div class="prose-dark mt-16">
        <h2 id="geo-relationship" class="anchor-top">Relationship to Generative Engine Optimisation (GEO)</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Generative search optimisation and generative engine optimisation (GEO) describe the same practice — the distinction is terminological, not substantive.</strong> GEO has emerged as the more established industry term, used consistently by practitioners, agencies, and emerging academic research on the discipline. "Generative search optimization" (with the US spelling) and "generative search optimisation" (British spelling) are the search queries many professionals use when researching the field, which is why this page exists — but the framework, tactics, and measurement approach are identical.
        </p>
        <p>
          Our <a href="/generative-engine-optimisation/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">complete GEO guide</a> is the authoritative reference for everything covered on this page and more — including the seven-step GEO framework, cross-model optimisation, citation monitoring methodology, and sector-specific applications. If you are researching generative search optimisation as a discipline, the GEO guide is the logical next read.
        </p>

        <h3>How GEO Relates to Other Disciplines</h3>
        <p>
          GEO sits alongside <a href="/what-is-geo/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">answer engine optimisation (AEO)</a> — which focuses on direct-answer formats like featured snippets and voice search — and traditional SEO, which remains foundational for the retrieval stage of generative search. The three disciplines are complementary: a strong SEO base improves retrieval probability; AEO-grade content structure improves synthesis and extraction; GEO-specific entity work and schema improve citation selection. For a detailed comparison with traditional SEO, see <a href="/geo-vs-seo/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO vs SEO</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          For the definition and scope of the broader GEO discipline: <a href="/geo-definition/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO definition</a>. For a plain-language explanation of what GEO involves: <a href="/geo-explained/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO explained</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Section 6: Measuring Visibility -->
      <div class="prose-dark mt-16">
        <h2 id="measuring-visibility" class="anchor-top">Measuring Generative Search Visibility</h2>
        <p>
          <strong>Generative search visibility requires a measurement framework built around citation rather than ranking — because the traditional SEO metrics of position, CTR, and organic sessions do not capture AI citation performance.</strong>
        </p>

        <h3>Citation Frequency</h3>
        <p>
          Citation frequency measures how often your brand or content appears in AI-generated answers for your target query set. Track this by running your priority queries against each major platform weekly and recording whether your brand appears in the response. A citation rate above 30% for core queries indicates strong generative search visibility.
        </p>

        <h3>Citation Accuracy</h3>
        <p>
          AI systems sometimes cite brands inaccurately — misattributing claims, confusing entities, or representing your positioning incorrectly. Citation accuracy monitoring checks not just whether you are cited, but whether the AI's representation of your brand is correct and favourable. Inaccurate citations can damage trust even when they appear frequently.
        </p>

        <h3>AI Share of Voice</h3>
        <p>
          AI share of voice measures your brand's citation proportion relative to competitors across your tracked query set. If your brand is cited in three of ten AI responses for a given query, your share of voice is 30%. Track this metric over time and against specific competitors to understand your competitive position in generative search.
        </p>

        <h3>AI Referral Traffic</h3>
        <p>
          As generative search platforms increasingly include clickable source links, direct referral traffic from AI platforms becomes a measurable outcome. In Google Analytics, segment referral traffic from chatgpt.com, perplexity.ai, copilot.microsoft.com, and bard.google.com to track visitors arriving via AI citations. This traffic tends to be high-intent — users who click through from an AI citation have already received a qualifying response about your brand.
        </p>

        <p>
          For professional monitoring support and a structured citation tracking programme, see our <a href="/geo-services/" class="text-accent-400 underline decoration-accent-500/30 underline-offset-2 hover:text-accent-300">GEO services</a>.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- FAQ -->
      <div class="prose-dark mt-16">
        <h2 id="faq" class="anchor-top">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      </div>

      <div class="mt-8 space-y-2" id="faq-accordion">
        {faqs.map(faq => (
          <div class="card overflow-hidden">
            <button
              type="button"
              class="flex w-full items-center justify-between p-5 text-left text-sm font-semibold text-white transition hover:bg-white/[.02]"
              aria-expanded="false"
            >
              <span>{faq.q}</span>
              <span class="faq-icon ml-4 shrink-0 text-[var(--accent)] transition-transform duration-200">+</span>
            </button>
            <div class="faq-body max-h-0 overflow-hidden transition-[max-height] duration-300 ease-in-out">
              <p class="px-5 pb-5 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-300">{faq.a}</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        ))}
      </div>

      <!-- Related Reading -->
      <div class="mt-16" id="related">
        <span class="eyebrow">Related reading</span>
        <div class="mt-6 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4">
          {related.map(item => (
            <a href={item.href} class="card card-hover block p-5 no-underline">
              <span class="eyebrow">{item.tag}</span>
              <h3 class="mt-2 font-display text-base font-semibold text-white">{item.title}</h3>
              <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-ink-300">{item.excerpt}</p>
              <span class="mt-3 inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-[var(--accent)]">Read guide <span aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></span>
            </a>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="relative border-t hair mt-12 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="dot-grid absolute inset-0 opacity-40" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="container-wide relative py-20 text-center">
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold grad-text md:text-4xl">Get Your Brand into AI Search Results</h2>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-5 max-w-xl text-ink-300 leading-relaxed">
        GEOoptimised delivers end-to-end generative search optimisation: from an initial AI visibility audit that shows exactly where you stand today, through to ongoing citation monitoring and competitive intelligence. We work across all five major AI search surfaces.
      </p>
      <div class="mt-8 flex flex-col items-center gap-4 sm:flex-row sm:justify-center">
        <a href="/contact/" class="btn btn-primary">Request a GEO audit</a>
        <a href="/geo-services/" class="btn btn-ghost">View GEO services</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <script>
    const faqBtns = document.querySelectorAll('#faq-accordion button');
    faqBtns.forEach(btn => {
      btn.addEventListener('click', () => {
        const body = btn.nextElementSibling as HTMLElement;
        const icon = btn.querySelector('.faq-icon') as HTMLElement;
        const open = btn.getAttribute('aria-expanded') === 'true';
        btn.setAttribute('aria-expanded', String(!open));
        if (open) {
          body.style.maxHeight = '0';
          icon.style.transform = 'rotate(0deg)';
        } else {
          body.style.maxHeight = body.scrollHeight + 'px';
          icon.style.transform = 'rotate(45deg)';
        }
      });
    });

    const tocLinks = document.querySelectorAll('#toc-nav a');
    const headings = Array.from(
      document.querySelectorAll('h2[id], h3[id]')
    ) as HTMLElement[];

    const observer = new IntersectionObserver(
      entries => {
        entries.forEach(entry => {
          if (entry.isIntersecting) {
            tocLinks.forEach(link => {
              link.classList.remove('text-[var(--accent)]');
              if (link.getAttribute('href') === '#' + entry.target.id) {
                link.classList.add('text-[var(--accent)]');
              }
            });
          }
        });
      },
      { rootMargin: '-20% 0px -70% 0px', threshold: 0 }
    );

    headings.forEach(h => observer.observe(h));
  </script>

</Base>
